In an irritated voice, "Ok, just drop it there, beside Dead-End." he 
doesn't bother looking up, he continues working. "Oh, and try not 
to draw too much attention to this place.


On 8 May 2001, at 20:55, robertdahl wrote:

> "Goood" Motormaster says to the small voice from Speedbreaker. He
> looked around, and saw Dead-End fall. He walked over, reached down,
> and hoisted him up. He then walked over to Switchblade. "Patch him up
> good enough to continue" he said in his gruff voice. He turned around,
> and transformed. Opening up his trailor, he reveiled certain robot
> parts. "Come on, you can use some part to replace him" he said,
> motioning to an arm piece.
